<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-04-22T01:35:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-04-22T01:35:00-05:00" n="45" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d45">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">123 EN 3/710: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Dreyfus</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-04-22T10:00:00+03:25">April 22,
                                    1942—10 a.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received noon.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>116. Afghan Minister informs me his Government has now given formal
                            consent to appointment of Engert as Envoy Extraordinary and Minister
                            Plenipotentiary of the United States at Kabul. I have asked him to
                            ascertain in view of this development whether his Government will now
                            grant permission for Thayer to proceed to Kabul to open the
                            Legation.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Dreyfus</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>